The coloration in life is characterized by a dark carapace with many aqua blue spots, black ocular peduncles mottled with sky blue blotches, corneas grey– black (
Fig. 2
). Front and epistome dark with many sky blue spots. Pterygostomial region violet–blue, becoming mottled with sky blue spots on branchiostegal region (
Fig. 2
); suborbital region sky blue with blotches of violet–blue. Ischium and merus of maxilliped sky blue with black blotches. Merus of cheliped brown to dark red with few sky blue spots on outer face and larger spots on inner face; carpus dark red, occasionally with sky blue spots; palm and dactylus bright red. Ambulatory legs with meri mottled sky blue and dark; carpus, propodus and dactylus with fewer or no sky blue spots. Colours fade quickly after preservation.
